definition.value: Any deviation from the normal number of basophils per volume in the blood circulation.
An abnormally increased count of basophils per volume in the blood circulation.
An abnormally reduced count of basophils per volume in the blood circulation.
A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).
Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.
A deviation from normal of the waist to hip ratio, defined as the waist measurement divided by hip measurement.
Any anomaly of a reflex, i.e., of an automatic response mediated by the nervous system (a reflex does not need the intervention of conscious thought to occur).

An anomaly of a reflex that is elicited as a motor response to scraping of the skin. They are generally graded as present or absent. They differ from tendon reflexes in that the sensory signal must ascend the spinal cord to reach the brain and then descend the spinal cord to reach the motor neurons.
Overshoot of downward saccadic eye movements.
Saccadic undershoot of upward saccadic eye movements, i.e., an upward saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object.
Presence of a chemical substance found within an individual that is not naturally produced or expected to be present in human tissues or bodily fluids.
The presence of a xenobiotic in urine.
Detection of methadone or its metabolite 2-ethylidene-1,5-dimethyl-3,3- diphenylpyrrolidine (EDDP) in urine.

Euphoria is an overwhelming and all-encompassing feeling of intense inner sense of joy, happiness, excitement, or elation that is far beyond and blatantly abnormal for what would typically be anticipated in the context or social circumstance. It is experienced as an unusual pleasurable feeling often with an inspirational sense of profound insight.
Any deviation from the normal sexual drive or desire for sexual activity.
A break or crush injury of the thigh bone (femur).
A reversal of sleeping habits, with a tendency to sleep during the day and be awake at night.
Any deviation from the normal ratio of the volume of red blood cells to the total volume of blood.
A reduction below the normal ratio of the volume of red blood cells to the total volume of blood.
